{ The course is organized as follows:  Before learning any theory, I suggest going through the chapter onKey Middlegame & Endgame Themes.  You can then get a bird's-eye view of the Scandinavian by learning theQuickstarter guide. }
1. e4 d5 2. exd5
{ 2.Nc3  The Van-Geet Opening together with  2.f3  ,  2.d3  ,  2.e5  and  2.Nf3  are covered inchapter 1.   2.d4  The bodacious Blackmar-Diemer Gambit is the topic ofchapter 2. }
2... Qxd5
{ The  2...Nf6  Scandi and the Portuguese Gambit are covered in abonus chapter. }
3. Nc3
{ 3.d4  and  3.c4  are discussed inchapter 3.   3.Nf3  is White's best alternative to  3.Nc3  , which is examined inchapter 4. }
3... Qa5 4. d4
{ Alternatives to 4. d4 such as   4.b4  ,  4.g3  ,  4.Nf3  and  4.Bc4  are covered inchapter 5. }
4... Nf6 5. Nf3
{ Sidelines such as  5.Bd3  ,  5.a3  ,  5.h3  and  5.Be2  are swiftly dealt with inchapter 6.   5.Bd2  is addressed inchapter 7.   5.Bc4  is analyzed inchapter 8. }
5... Bf5 6. Bc4
{ is the absolute mainline, which is thoroughly examined inchapter 11.   6.Bd2  and  6.Bd3  sidelines are tackled inchapter 9.   6.Ne5  is the focus ofchapter 10.  The course includes a chapter with10 annotated model games. It finishes with100+ thematic tactical puzzles taken from games in the Scandinavian. }
