{ This is the right place for the queen. Dropping it back with ...Qd6 or ...Qd8 is far more passive and totally uncalled for. }
4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 { is the mainline. } 5... Bf5 6. Ne5
{ is one of White's most challenging variations in the entire ...Qa5 Scandinavian complex. It's connected with a whole host of ideas, ranging from g4 and Bc4 to Nc4. }
6... c6 7. Nc4 Qd8
{ It's true Black has lost a bit of time with the queen. On the other hand, White's knight on c4 is far from ideally placed.   And not  7...Qc7  because of  8.Qf3  Bg6  9.Bf4±  with yet another tempo on the queen. Black has big issues here. }
8. Be2 h6
{ is a good prophylactic move, creating a square for the light-squared bishop on h7. This takes the sting out of any g4 + h4 shenanigans. }
9. O-O e6 10. Bf4 Be7
{ Coming up are ...O-O and ...Nd7-b6 when Black has a perfectly fine position without any weaknesses. }
