1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. d4 Nc6 4. Nf3
{ In this informational line, I'm going to point out why I opted not to recommend }
4... Bg4
{ This is most popular move but I wasn't completely satisfied with Black's position following 5. Nc3.   4...e5  is my recommendation. }
5. Nc3
{ Forces Black's queen away from the center of the board.   5.Be2  O-O-O  is a direct transposition to the3. Nf3 variation. }
5... Qh5 6. d5 O-O-O 7. Be2 Bxf3
{ 7...e6  runs into  8.Ng5!  Bxe2  9.Qxe2  Qxe2+  10.Kxe2±  with a double-attack on the f7 pawn and c6 knight. Black has big problems in this endgame. }
8. Bxf3 Qe5+ 9. Be3 e6 10. O-O Nf6 11. dxc6 Rxd1 12. cxb7+ Kb8 13. Raxd1
{ White has a rook, a bishop and a super strong pawn on b7! While Black should be able to hold this, it's not straightforward and absolutely no fun. }
