5... Bxf3 6. Bxf3 Qe6+
{ forces the queens off the board and Black is certainly not worse in the ensuing endgame. }
7. Qe2
{ is the only serious move.   7.Be2  Nd4=  followed by ...Qxe2 leads to a completely equal endgame. }
7... Qxe2+ 8. Kxe2 Nd4+ { Oops. White just stepped into a triple fork. } 9. Kd1
Nxf3 10. gxf3 e6
{ White's kingside pawn structure is in shambles. Black is clearly for choice. }
