Nxe4 18. dxe4 Rxe4
{ White's bishop is hanging and White's most natural move to protect it is }
19. Rfe1
{ Alternatives are considered below and there's only one move that objectively equalizes with White  (yes you read that right, White's the one that needs to be extremely careful here)  .   19.Qxa7??  loses on the spot to  Rxe2  20.Qa8+  Ke7-+  White has run out of checks and is a clean piece down. He can resign.   19.Bd3?  runs into the intermezzo  Bxf3!  20.Qxa7  Re5  21.Qb8+   21.Rxb6?  Bc6!−+  leaves Black with an extra piece.  21...Qc8∓  The resulting endgame is clearly better for Black.   19.Nxd4!?  is strongly met by  Bxe2  Following  20.Nxe2  Bd6  21.Nc3  Re5!  with the idea ...Ra5 is very strong.  22.Nb5   22.Rfd1  Ra5  23.Qd3  Kc8  24.Nb5  Kb8=+  White's threats are over and he's simply worse.  22...Ke7  23.c4  Bc5=+  White's attack is over. Our queen is coming to c6, the h8 rook to d8 and our king is perfectly safe on e7.   Remarkably  19.Bd1!  is the only move that maintains the balance. Good luck finding that one OTB!  c6   19...Bxf3  20.Bxf3  Re5=  is also totally playable if you want to test White more. ...Bc5 is coming next and White once again has no attack as our king will simply hide on e7.  20.Nxd4  This hard to spot move forces a draw after  Bxd1  21.Nxc6+  Qxc6  22.Rfxd1+  Bd6  23.Qxa7  Rhe8  24.Rxd6+!  Needless to say, only an engine would play like this.  Qxd6  25.Qa8+  Kc7  26.Qa7+=  with a perpetual. Good luck finding all those hard moves with White, this is a nightmare line for White in practical play. }
19... c6
{ Covers the a7 pawn. White will struggly to find any compensation whatsoever. }
20. Nxd4
{ 20.Red1  Bd6  21.Nxd4  Bxe2  22.Nxe2  Re5  23.Nd4  Ra5⩱  is also better for Black. }
20... Rxd4 21. Bxh5 Bc5
{ Opposite colored bishops are on the board and the only one attacking here will be Black with ...Rd2 coming.   Best play by both sides follows  22.c3  Rd2  23.Be2  Qc7  24.Rbd1  Rxd1  25.Rxd1+  Ke7  26.Qd3  g6  27.Qe4+  Kf6  28.Bg4  Rd8  29.Rxd8  Qxd8  30.Qxc6+  Kg7  with an endgame White should hold. }
