6. h3
{ puts the question to the bishop. Should we take on f3 or retreat the bishop? }
6... Bh5
{ is the correct response. The rule is: When White puts the question to our bishop with h2-h3, we should only play ...Bxf3 if we can follow up with ...Nd4. Otherwise, we should retreat the bishop with ...Bh5   6...Bxf3  7.Bxf3  hits our queen, meaning we are unable to follow up with ... Nd4.  7...Qd7  8.c3±  gives White a clear advantage. Not only does it prevent ...Nd4 but also prepares d4 and Qb3, which will put our queenside under pressure. }
