17. Bxd5 Bxd5 18. Nf4
{ is an important move, which I doubt many of your opponents will find.   18.Nxa8?  is far worse since Black ends up with an extra tempo compared to the text after  18...b5  19.Nf4  Bxa8∓ }
18... Bc6 19. Nxa8 b5
{ Black will capture the knight on the next turn. We have full compensation for the exchange due to White's numerous weaknesses on the light-squares. If there's a side that's better, it's Black. }
