{ 23.Nxe4  cannot be recommended. After  23...dxe4  24.Qxe4  Bxb4⩱  Black is better as White's pawns are overextended. Note that  25.Rfb1  is easily met with  25...c5! }
23... Qa7 24. Rfc1
{ Negi stopped here saying it's not exactly clear how White can improve. }
24... Rfd8
{ I agree. Black can chop on c5 at an opportune moment when the ensuing opposite-colored bishop position is very drawish. White's queenside pawns are firmly blockaded and a caveman-style pawn storm on the kingside can easily backfire. At high depth, the engines give Black full equality and I'm not one to overrule them. }
