{ 9...Nc6  is another good option. After  10.Be3  Na5  11.O-O  Nxb3  12.axb3  Be7  13.Nf4  O-O=  Black is doing well with ...Rfd8 coming next. }
10. Be3 O-O
{ Black is very comfortable and can engineer the ...c5 break with ...Na6 and ...Rd8 next.   The simplest reply to  11.Nf4  , intending to meet ...c5 with d5, is  11...c6  with the idea ...Nd5.  12.O-O   12.Nd3  is well met by  Na6  when ...c5 is coming next.  12...Nd5  13.Nfxd5  cxd5=  is very comfortable for Black.   11.Nf4  c5  is also fully playable. White can push ahead with  12.d5  but  e5  is a nice reply, knocking back White's knight.  13.Nd3  Qc7  threatening ...b5. If  14.Bc4  then  b5!  anyhow is very strong with the idea  15.Bxb5  c4  16.Bxd7  Nbxd7  17.Nf2  Rab8  when White should give up the b2 pawn.  18.O-O   18.Rb1  runs into  Bb4  threatening Nxd5  19.Bd2  Nb6=+  and the d-pawn will fall.  18...Rxb2=  Black is doing very well. }
