{ connected with Bc4 is one of White's best approaches in the Scandinavian. The bishop is very well placed on d2, not only breaking the pin but also x-raying Black's queen. }
5... Bg4 6. f3 Bd7
{ The bishop is much better placed here than on  6...Bf5  where it is exposed to  7.g4  Bg6  8.f4!  when Black is in trouble. For example  8...e6  9.f5!  exf5  10.Qe2+±  gives White a big advantage }
