{ comes with the deadly threat of Nd5 so Black should drop the queen back to safety with 7...Qb6.   7.f3  is well met by  7...Bf5  and if  8.g4  then simply  8...Bg6  9.h4  h6  10.Bd2  Now Black should retreat the queen with  10...Qb6  and meet  11.a4  with  11...a6=  with ideas of ...Nc6 and O-O-O. Black has a fine position. }
7... Qb6 8. O-O c6
{ If White's knight were on f3, the bishop on g4 could be targeted with h3, g4 and Ne5/Nh4. As is, with the knight on e2, Black is very solid and has no particular problems. }
