{ The queen is very safe on a5 as the a3 pawn will always be hanging if White pushes ahead with b4.   Here are a couple of sample lines:  16.Ra1?!  is dubious.   Instead White should prefer  16.Bc7  when  16...Rd7  17.Be5  c5=  gives Black a good game.  16...Ne4!  17.Nxe4  Qxd2  18.Nxd2  Rxd4-+  Forks White's knight and bishop. Black is winning.   16.Qc1  also fails to endanger our queen after  16...c5!= }
