e6
{ Black had a more than acceptable position in the game ½-½ @@StartBracket@@68@@EndBracket@@ Pikula,D @@StartBracket@@2476@@EndBracket@@-Zhukova,N  @@StartBracket@@2471@@EndBracket@@ Belgrade 2000.   The bishop on b3 is restricted and White's g-pawn strikes me as nothing but a weakness.   A sample continuation is  12.Bd2  Bb4  13.g5  Nd5  14.Nxd5  Bxd2+  15.Qxd2  Qxd2+  16.Kxd2  exd5=  is equal. I'd even take Black here since White's bishop is completely restricted. Another good option  is  16...cxd5  if you want to unbalance the pawn structure. Here Black can play for the full point with breaks like ...h6. }
