[White "10. 3.Nc3 | 5.Nf3 6.Ne5"]
[Black "Memory marker #2"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "rn2kb1r/pp3ppp/2p1pn2/q3Nb2/2BP4/2N5/PPP2PPP/R1BQK2R w KQkq - 0 8"]
[SetUp "1"]

8. Bd2 { White has just played Bd2, x-raying our queen. Should we be worried? }
8... Nbd7
{ Nope, White has no good discoveries and Black should instead seek to immediately exchange off White's dangerous e5 knight, which supports moves like g2-g4 and h2-h4 to chase down our light-squared bishop.  Rule to remember:  Black does best in eliminating White's powerful knight at the earliest opportunity!  Rule to remember: White's discovered attack on our queen often loses its sting if we have already played ...c6, which creates squares on c7 and d8 for our majesty to retreat to. }
