12... gxf6 13. O-O Nd7 14. Re1
{ has never occurred in practice. The verdictis Black is completely fine after }
14... O-O-O 15. c4 Ne5
{ Exchanging the knights solves all of Black's problems. } 16. Nxe5 Bxd5 17.
cxd5 fxe5
{ The minor pieces have all been vacuumed off the board. The b2 pawn is hanging and if White doesn't take it then ...f6 will cover the e5 pawn. Black is completely fine. }
