8. a3
{ is considered a critical variation in the ...Qa5 Scandinavian. White picks up the bishop pair, but I'm about to prove he is fine. }
8... Bxc3 9. Bxc3 Qb6 10. d5
{ was Wesley So's recommendation in his Lifetime Repertoire. This is a line where White is playing for two results but with precise play, Black can make a draw fairly easily. }
10... exd5 11. Bxd5 Be6
{ It's important to get the light-squared bishops off the board here. This move was not considered in the book Kaufman's Repertoire for White and Black by GM Larry Kaufman. }
12. Bxe6 { Capturing the bishop is more challenging than  12.Bxf6 } 12... Qxe6+
13. Qe2 Qxe2+ 14. Kxe2 Nbd7
{ White is slightly better, better having a bishop versus a knight in a relatively open position with pawns on both flanks. Nevertheless, Black can hold this endgame without too much trouble. Let's see exactly how to do that: }
15. Rhe1 O-O-O 16. Kf1
{ is White's best move, threatening both Ng5 and Re7 to go after the f7 pawn. }
16... h6 { It's important to stop Ng5. } 17. b3
{ was Wesley So's improvement over the Karjakin-Mamedyarov game but I'm not impressed. }
17... Rhe8 18. Bb2 Rxe1+
{ As usual, exchanging rooks gets Black ever closer to a draw. } 19. Rxe1 Re8
20. Rd1 { Now } 20... b6
{ is Black's best move and was not considered in the Chessable course Lifetime Repertoires: Wesley So's 1. e4 Part 1. It creates luft and puts yet another pawn on a dark square, reducing the scope of White's bishop.   Wesley only mentioned  20...c5  which makes little sense. There's absolutely no reason to weaken the d6 square and give White something to work with after  21.Nd2  Kc7  22.Nc4  Re6  23.Bc1+=  Wesley correctly points out White has some pressure with Bf4+ and can exploit the weak d6 square. It's however easy to avoid all this with 20...b6. }
21. Nd4
{ White's knight is heading to f5 and, if allowed it to reach this square, it would cause some problems. }
21... g6 { White can hop into c6 with } 22. Nc6 { but after } 22... a6
{ The knight will be promptly kicked back with ...Re6. White hasn't achieved anything significant with this knight tour. }
