{ is Black's best move and was not considered in the Chessable course Lifetime Repertoires: Wesley So's 1. e4 Part 1. It creates luft and puts yet another pawn on a dark-square, reducing the scope of White's bishop.  Wesley only mentions   20...c5  which makes little sense. There's absolutely no reason to weaken the d6 square and give White something to work with after  21.Nd2  Kc7  22.Nc4  Re6  23.Bc1+=  Wesley correctly points out White has some pressure with Bf4+ and can exploit the weak d6 square. It's however easy to avoid all this with 20...b6. }
