a3 Bxc3 9. Bxc3 Qb6
{ After concluding that  10.d5  does not yield White an advantage, it's finally time to address White's most common and natural move in this position: }
10. O-O Nc6
{ is an important move.   The point is that Black prevents  11.d5  which is now strongly met by  11...O-O-O!   White has tried many moves at this juncture but only  11.b4  and  11.a4  are really worth reviewing.  We are going to go over all of White's main tries for completeness's sake and, while it's good to see them once as I will be pointing out several important middlegame themes, feel free to pause most of them afterward. }
