11. Bd3 { has been played a handful of times. } 11... Bg4 12. h3 Bxf3 13. Qxf3
{ White has two bishops vs two knights, which is hardly impressive given how passive White's bishop on c3 is. Moreover, this comes at the cost of the d4 pawn: }
13... Nxd4 14. Bxd4 Qxd4 15. Qxb7 O-O 16. Rab1 Qb6
{ There's no reason Black should be any worse here. White is more than welcome to fix our pawn structure with Qxb6 and if he instead retreats the queen, then ...a5-a4 to fix the weak b2 pawn will follow with good play along the b-file. With a rook tied down to the defense of the b2 pawn, White can never be better. }
