{ Gets the queen out of the x-ray while threatening mate on g2.   11...Qf5  to attack the  d3  pawn is also possible and was played in the correspondence game ½-½ @@StartBracket@@59@@EndBracket@@ Posylek, C @@StartBracket@@2295@@EndBracket@@-Pecot, L @@StartBracket@@2487@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 1999. The text is even stronger. }
12. Ng3 h5
{ with full compensation for the pawn. Black threatening to drop back the queen back to g6 and then follow up with ...h4 and a huge attack.   White should get the queens off the board with  13.Qxg4  hxg4  but now the d3 pawn is hanging, forcing  14.Rd1  Bd6⭡  Black is planning to double up on the h-file with ...Rh7 and ...Rdh8. White's kingside is about to come under serious pressure. }
