{ is White's most popular time. Despite being 5 times more common than the alternatives, White is already losing after this move!   8.Ne2  is White's best choice although he's still not in the clear after  8...Nb4=  which threatens to jump into d3 and c2.   8.d5??  isn't any better. After  8...Nb4  9.Na3  Bc5  White is in big trouble with ...Re8+ coming next. For example  10.Be2  Re8  11.Kf1  Nh5  12.g4  Rxe2  13.Qxe2  Bd3-+  pins and wins. White can resign. }
8... Bb4+ 9. Nc3 Re8 10. Kf2
{ 10.Qd2  loses to  10...Qxd4  11.Qxd4  Nxd4  12.O-O-O  Rxe3  13.Rxd4  Bxc3  14.bxc3  Rae8-+  White is busted. There's no defense against ...Re1+ or ... Rxc3+. }
10... Rxe3 { This exchange sac once again works wonders! } 11. Kxe3 Bc2
{ The bishop is untouchable as } 12. Qxc2 Qxd4+ 13. Ke2 Re8+ { is decisive. } *

