1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6
{ The 2...Nf6 Scandinavian is objectively dubious, but a good blitz and rapid weapon nonetheless. White has to be quite precise in order to get an advantage with Black having a whole array of devious tricks and traps at his disposal. }
3. c4 { Reinforcing the d5 pawn is White's third most common move. } 3... c6 4.
dxc6 { Accepting the Gambit cannot be recommended. } 4... Nxc6
{ is a turbocharged version of the Danish Gambit with White having played c2-c4, which critically weakened the d4 square. }
5. Nc3 e5 6. d3 Bb4
{ Black is ready for ...O-O and ...Bf5 with more than enough compensation for the pawn deficit. The d3 pawn is a big target and the d4 square a fantastic outpost for Black's knight.   A sample continuation is  7.Nf3  O-O  8.Be2  Here  8...e4!  already works well.  9.dxe4  Qxd1  10.Bxd1  Nxe4  11.O-O  Nxc3  12.bxc3  Bxc3=  restores material equality with an excellent position. }
